name: I'M ALWAYS IN HIM.
description: (Geez...you went from a triangle of people cannibalizing each other to this?) Yup, I sure did and get your mind out of the gutter because it's not what you think on this one. You all immediately thought it was a sexual innuendo. Well, it is and it and it isn't. It's both. On the surface is appears to be a perpetual proclamation of sexual conquest, but let's look deeper (sigh, another sex pun). The letters IM are actually always in the word HIM. You cannot have the word HIM without those letters. So, the sentence is is technically true. IM is ALWAYS IN HIM. The use of the apostrophe in the I'M delineates the possessive of I am, thus creating the perceived sexual innuendo. And that concludes this session of pedantic balderdash you may now turn the page.
